Reasoning: The paper deals with a discrete process for curve shortening in the presence of obstacles, which is a problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses the behavior of the process on regular grids and random point sets, which falls under the category of computational geometry and graphics (cs.GR). The properties of the process, such as invariance under affine transformations and preservation of convexity, suggest that it may have applications in dynamical systems (cs.DS) and scientific computing (cs.SI). Finally, the experimental results and analysis of the process involve numerical simulations and data analysis, which could fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
